overview: The user initiated a request for thorough browser-based testing of the
  sleep questionnaire application. The agent systematically tested the
  application's core functionalities, including the questionnaire's navigation,
  validation, and conditional fields, as well as report generation (PDF
  download) and the admin dashboard's authentication and error handling. API
  endpoints for responses, PDF generation, and CSV export were also verified.
  During testing, the agent utilized a "Pre-fill & Jump to Report (Dev)" button
  to expedite the process. After completing the testing, the agent provided a
  detailed summary of findings, highlighting correctly working features, minor
  issues like ESLint warnings and an outdated page title, and offering
  recommendations. Subsequently, the agent addressed these issues by updating
  the page title and committing several significant feature enhancements, such
  as new fields for pain and chronic fatigue screening, an improved mental
  health section, a comprehensive report with advanced sleep analysis, updated
  PDF generation, and a robust CSV export feature, all following conventional
  commit guidelines.
